                    "description": "Topic: interface analysis and control in Mo/Si multilayer systems.\n\nI mainly worked on the characterization of surfaces and interfaces, and the physical and chemical processes occurring there. I used a wide range of analysis techniques, including ion spectroscopy (LEIS), X-ray Photoelectron Spectroscopy (XPS), X-ray reflection and diffraction (XRD, GIXR), and Transmission Electron Microscopy (TEM).\n\nThe work included three weeks of beam-time at the ESRF synchrotron radiation facility in Grenoble, as well as two weeks at the BESSY synchrotron radiation facility in Berlin.\n\nI supervised one Bachelor student and one Master student.\n\nI obtained the degree of doctor upon defending my Ph.D. thesis on the 1st of October 2010.\n\nAttended conferences:\n- VEIT 15th International Summer School, 17-21 September 2007, Sozopol, Bulgaria (poster)\n- 9th PXRMS, 3-7 February 2008, Big Sky Resort, Montana (oral)\n- 14th ICSFS, 29 June \u2013 4 July 2008, Dublin (poster)\n- Workshop on High Energy Photoemission, 3 Dec 2008, BESSY, Berlin (oral) plus the BESSY user meeting on 4 Dec 2008.\n- 2009 International Symposium on Extreme Ultraviolet Lithography, 18-21 October 2009, Prague (poster).",
